SIMPLE: bin
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bin
<hw>Bin</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>binne</ets>,
AS. <ets>binn</ets> manager, crib; perh. akin to D. <ets>ben</ets>,
<ets>benne</ets>, basket, and to L. <ets>benna</ets> a kind of carriage
( a Gallic word), W. <ets>benn</ets>, <ets>men</ets>, wain, cart.]</ety>
<def>A box, frame, crib, or inclosed place, used as a receptacle for any
commodity; <as>as, a corn <ex>bin</ex>; a wine <ex>bin</ex>; a coal
<ex>bin</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bin</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bin
<hw>Bin</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Binned</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Binning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To put into a bin; <as>as, to
<ex>bin</ex> wine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bin</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Bin
<hw>Bin</hw>. <def>An old form of <er>Be</er> and <er>Been</er>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bin-</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Bin-
<hw>Bin-</hw>. <def>A euphonic form of the prefix
<er>Bi-</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Binal</ent>⟦br⟧
